print-ruby-configure-args:

	prints the compile time and configuration arguments used when ruby was 
	compiled

update-ruby-environment:

	updates rbenv, ruby-build, and rbenv-gem-rehash

install_ruby:

	A simple wrapper around rbenv and ruby-build to facilitate building and 
	installing ruby with CFLAGS and the openssl available throught homebrew. 
	Ruby 2.0.0-* is not supported since rbenv and ruby-build install the 
	openssl dependency as needed. 

	prerequisites:
		- bash-completion
		- rbenv
		- ruby-build

	How-To:
		- run sh install.sh
		(scripts install to ~/bin and completion scripts to 
		 /usr/local/etc/bash_completion.d/)
		
		- install_ruby [version]
		will auto completed to the versions available from ruby-build
